<h1>Vegetarian Casserole</h1>
<p>Known as "buddha's delight", the original recipe for this dish lists 18 different ingredients to represent tge 18 buddhas. Although the ingredients may seem unusual, they are all easy to obtain at Asian markets</p>

</body>
</html> 
<ol>
    <li>2 ozs dried bean-curd skins</li>
    <li>2-oz package cellophane noodles</li>
    <li>1 cup loosely packed tiger lily buds</li>
    <li>4-6 dried Chinese mushrooms</li>
    <li>A few lettuce leaves</li>
    <li>1/4 cup each drained and sliced canned bamboo shoots and water chestnuts</li>
    <li>10-oz can braised gluten, drained abd cut into chunks</li>
    <li>2 tbs light soy sauce</li>
    <li>1 tb rice wine</li>
    <li>1 cup Chinese stock or water</li>
    <li>1/2 cup broccoli florets</li>
    <li>1/2 tsp sesame oil</li>

  </ol> 

  <ol>
    <li>Soak the bean-curd skins in hot water for 2-3 hours, drain, and cut into short sections. Soak the next 3 ingredients in separate bowls of warm water for 30 minutes. Drian. Line a sandpot or flameproof casserloe with the lettuce leaves</li>
    <li>Put the soaked and drained ingredients and the bamboo shoots, water chestnuts, and gluten on top of the lettuce. Add the soy sauce, rice wine, and stock or water and stir to blend. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer gently for 20-25 minutes.</li>
    <li>Add the broccoli florets and stir to mix well. Replace the lid and continue simmering gently for 5-10 minutes. Finally, sprinkle the sesame oil over the vegtables. Serve hot, straight from the sandpot or Casserole</li>
  </ol>
